obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (70368)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70368&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Delhi Rent Control Act,`
  line 1958.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the areas included within the limits of the New Delhi Municipal Committee and the`
  line `Delhi Cantonment Board and to such urban areas within the limits of the Municipal Corporation of Delhi`
  line `as are specified in the First Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, by notification^1`
  line `in the Official Gazette, extend this Act or`
  line `any provision thereof, to any other urban area included within the limits of the Municipal Corporation of`
  line `Delhi of exclude any area from the operation of this Act or any provision thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Extended to the former Najafgarh and Narela N.A.C. areas and to other notified localities vide Notification No. G.S.R. 486,`
  line `dated 12.4.1962, Gazette of India, Pt. II, s. 3(i) page 449.`
  line
  line `2. 9th February, 1959, vide Notification No. S.O. 269, dated 31-1-1959, Gazette of India, pt. II, Sec. 3(ii), p. 331.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (70369)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 1976, s. 2, for clause (l) (w.e.f. 1-12-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70369&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "basic rent", in relation to premises let out before the 2nd day of June, 1944, means the basic rent`
  line `of such premises as determined in accordance with the provisions of the Second Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) "Controller" means a Controller appointed under sub-section (1) of section 35 and includes an`
  line `additional Controller appointed under sub-section (2) of that section;`
  line
  line `(c) "fair rate" means the fair rate fixed under section 31 and includes the rate as revised under`
  line `section 32;`
  line
  line `(d) "hotel or lodging house" means a building or part of a building where lodging with or without board`
  line `or other services is provided for a monetary consideration;`
  line
  line `(e) "landlord" means a person who, for the time being is receiving, or is entitled to receive, the rent of`
  line `any premises, whether on his own account or on account of or on behalf of, or for the benefit of, any other`
  line `person or as a trustee, guardian or receiver for any other person or who would so receive the rent or be`
  line `entitled to receive the rent, if the premises were let to a tenant;`
  line
  line `(f) "lawful increase" means an increase in rent permitted under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "manager of a hotel" includes any person in charge of the management of the hotel;`
  line
  line `(h) "owner of a lodging house" means a person who receives or is entitled to receive whether on his`
  line `own account or on behalf of himself and others or as an agent or a trustee for any other person, any monetary`
  line `consideration from any person on account of board, lodging or other services provided in the lodging house;`
  line
  line `(i) "premises" means any building or part of a building which is, or is intended to be, let separately for`
  line `use as a residence or for commercial use or for any other purpose, and includes,--`
  line
  line `(i) the garden, grounds and outhouses, if any, appertaining to such building or part of the building;`
  line
  line `(ii) any furniture supplied by the landlord for use in such building or part of the building;`
  line `but does not include a room in a hotel or lodging house;`
  line
  line `(j) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) "standard rent", in relation to any premises, means the standard rent referred to in section 6 or where`
  line `the standard rent has been increased under section 7, such increased rent;`
  line
  line `^1[(l) "tenant" means any person by whom or on whose account or behalf the rent of any premises is, or,`
  line `but for a special contract, would be, payable, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a sub-tenant;`
  line
  line `(ii) any person continuing in possession after the termination of his tenancy; and`
  line
  line `(iii) in the event of the death of the person continuing in possession after the termination of his`
  line `tenancy, subject to the order of succession and conditions specified, respectively, in Explanation I and`
  line `Explanation II to this clause, such of the aforesaid person’s--`
  line
  line `(a) spouse,`
  line
  line `(b) son or daughter, or, where there are both son and daughter, both of them,`
  line
  line `(c) parents,`
  line
  line `(d) daughter-in-law, being the widow of his pre-deceased son,`
  line
  line `as had been ordinarily living in the premises with such person as a member or members of his family up to`
  line `the date of his death, but does not include,--`
  line
  line `(A) any person against whom an order or decree for eviction has been made, except where such decree`
  line `or order for eviction is liable to be re-opened under the proviso to section 3 of the Delhi Rent Control`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1976 (18 of 1976);`
  line
  line `(B) any person to whom a licence, as defined by section 52 of the Indian Easements`
  line `Act, 1882 (5 of 1882), has been granted.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--The order of succession in the event of the death of the person continuing in possession`
  line `after the termination of his tenancy shall be as follows:--`
  line
  line `(a) firstly, his surviving spouse;`
  line
  line `(b) secondly, his son or daughter, or both, if there is no surviving spouse, or if the surviving spouse did`
  line `not ordinarily live with the deceased person as a member of his family up to the date of his death;`
  line
  line `(c) thirdly, his parents, if there is no surviving spouse, son or daughter of the deceased person, or if`
  line `such surviving spouse, son or daughter or any of them, did not ordinarily live in the premises as a member`
  line `of the family of the deceased person up to the date of his death; and`
  line
  line `(d) fourthly, his daughter-in-law, being the widow of his pre-deceased son, if there is no surviving`
  line `spouse, son, daughter or parents of the deceased person, or if such surviving spouse, son, daughter or`
  line `parents, or any of them, did not ordinarily live in the premises as a member of the family of the deceased`
  line `person up to the date of his death.`
  line
  line `Explanation II. ---If the person, who acquires, by succession, the right to continue in possession after`
  line `the termination of the tenancy, was not financially dependent on the deceased person on the date of his`
  line `death, such successor shall acquire such right for a limited period of one year; and, on the expiry of that`
  line `period, or on his death, whichever is earlier, the right of such successor to continue in possession after the`
  line `termination of the tenancy shall become extinguished.`
  line
  line `Explanation III.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that,--`
  line
  line `(a) where, by reason of Explanation II, the right of any successor to continue in possession after the`
  line `termination of the tenancy becomes extinguished, such extinguishment shall not affect the right of any other`
  line `successor of the same category to continue in possession after the termination of the tenancy; but if there is`
  line `no other successor of the same category, the right to continue in possession after the termination of the`
  line `tenancy shall not, on such extinguishment, pass on to any other successor, specified in any lower category`
  line `or categories, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) the right of every successor, referred to in Explanation I, to continue in possession after the`
  line `termination of the tenancy, shall be personal to him and shall not, on the death of such successor, devolve`
  line `on any of his heirs;]`
  line
  line `(m) "urban area" has the same meaning as in the Delhi Municipal Corporation Act, 1957 (66 of 1957).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (70370)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Act not to apply to certain premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70370&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall apply--`
  line
  line `(a) to any premises belonging to the Government; ^1***`
  line
  line `(b) to any tenancy or other like relationship created by a grant from the Government in respect of the`
  line `premises taken on lease, or requisitioned, by the Government:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that where any premises belonging to Government have been or are lawfully let by any`
  line `person by virtue of an agreement with the Government or otherwise, then, notwithstanding any judgment,`
  line `decree or order of any court or other authority, the provisions of this Act shall apply to such tenancy].`
  line
  line `^3[(c) to any premises, whether residential or not, whose monthly rent exceeds three thousand and five`
  line `hundred rupees; or`
  line
  line `(d) to any premises constructed on or after the commencement of the Delhi Rent Control (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1988, for a period of ten years from the date of completion of such construction;]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (70371)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Rent in excess of standard rent not recoverable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70371&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Except where rent is liable to periodical`
  line `increase by virtue of an agreement entered into before the 1st day of January, 1939, no tenant shall,`
  line `notwithstanding any agreement to the contrary, be liable to pay to his landlord for the occupation of any`
  line `premises any amount in excess of the standard rent of the premises, unless such amount is a lawful increase`
  line `of the standard rent in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1) any agreement for the payment of rent in excess of the`
  line `standard rent shall be construed as if it were an agreement for the payment of the standard rent only.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (70372)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Unlawful charges not to be claimed or received.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70372&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, no`
  line `person shall claim or receive any rent in excess of the standard rent, notwithstanding any agreement to the`
  line contrary.
  line
  line `(2) No person shall, in consideration of the grant, renewal or continuance of a tenancy or sub-tenancy`
  line `of any premises,--`
  line
  line `(a) claim or receive the payment of any sum as premium or pugree or claim or receive any`
  line `consideration whatsoever, in cash or in kind, in addition to the rent; or`
  line
  line `(b) except with the previous permission of the Controller, claim or receive the payment of any sum`
  line `exceeding one month's rent of such premises as rent in advance.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall not be lawful for the tenant or any other person acting or purporting to act on behalf of the`
  line `tenant or a sub-tenant to claim or receive any payment in consideration of the relinquishment, transfer or`
  line
  line `assignment of his tenancy or sub-tenancy, as the case may be, of any premises.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall apply--`
  line
  line `(a) to any payment made in pursuance of an agreement entered into before the 1st day of January,`
  line `1939; or`
  line
  line `(b) to any payment made under an agreement by any person to a landlord for the purpose of`
  line `financing the construction of the whole or part of any premises on the land belonging to, or taken on`
  line `lease by, the landlord, if one of the conditions of the agreement is that the landlord is to let to that`
  line `person the whole or part of the premises when completed for the use of that person or any member of`
  line `his family:`
  line
  line `Provided that such payment does not exceed the amount of agreed rent for a period of five years of the`
  line `whole or part of the premises to be let to such person.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of clause (b) of this sub-section, a "member of the family" of a person`
  line `means, in the case of an undivided Hindu family, any member of the family of that person and in the case`
  line `of any other family, the husband, wife, son daughter, father, mother, brother, sister or any other relative`
  line `dependent on that person.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (70373)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Standard rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70373&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), "standard rent", in relation to any`
  line `premises means--`
  line
  line `(A) in the case of residential premises--`
  line
  line `(1) where such premises have been let out at any time before the 2nd day of June, 1944,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the basic rent of such premises per annum does not exceed six hundred rupees, the`
  line `basic rent; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the basic rent of such premises per annum exceeds six hundred rupees, the basic rent`
  line `together with ten per cent. of such basic rent;`
  line
  line `(2) where such premises have been let out at any time on or after the 2nd day of`
  line `June, 1944,--`
  line
  line `(a) in any case where the rent of such premises has been fixed under the Delhi and`
  line `Ajmer-Merwara Rent Control Act, 1947 (19 of 1947), or the Delhi and Ajmer Rent Control Act,`
  line `1952 (38 of 1952),--`
  line
  line `(i) if such rent per annum does not exceed twelve hundred rupees, the rent so fixed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if such rent per annum exceeds twelve hundred rupees, the rent so fixed together with`
  line `ten per cent. of such rent;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, the rent calculated on the basis of ^1[ten per cent.] per annum of the`
  line `aggregate amount of the ^2[actual] cost of construction and the market price of the land comprised`
  line `in the premises on the date of the commencement of the construction;`
  line
  line `^3* * * *`
  line
  line `(B) in the case of premises other than residential premises--`
  line
  line `(1) where the premises have been let out at any time before the 2nd day of June, 1944, the basic`
  line `rent of such premises together with ten per cent. of such basic rent:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the rent so calculated exceeds twelve hundred rupees per annum, this`
  line `clause shall have effect as if for the words ten per cent., the words fifteen per cent. had been`
  line substituted;
  line
  line `(2) where the premises have been let out at any time on or after the 2nd day of June, 1944,--`
  line
  line `(a) in any case where the rent of such premises has been fixed under the Delhi and AjmerMerwara Rent Control Act, 1947 (19 of 1947) or the Delhi and Ajmer Rent Control Act, 1952 (38`
  line `of 1952),--`
  line
  line `(i) if such rent per annum does not exceed twelve hundred rupees, the rent so fixed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if such rent per annum exceeds twelve hundred rupees, the rent so fixed together with`
  line `fifteen per cent. of such rent;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, the rent calculated on the basis of ^4t[en per cent.] per annum of the`
  line `aggregate amount of the ^5t[actual] cost of construction and the market price of the land comprised`
  line `in the premises on the date of the commencement of the construction:`
  line
  line `^6[* * * *]`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1),`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of any premises, whether residential or not, constructed on or after the 2nd day of`
  line `June, 1951, but before the 9th day of June, 1955, the annual rent calculated with reference to the rent`
  line `at which the premises were let for the month of March, 1958, or if they were not so let, with reference`
  line `to the rent at which they were last let out, shall be deemed to be the standard rent for a period of seven`
  line `years from the date of the completion of the construction of such premises;`
  line
  line `^7[* * * *]`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any premises, whether residential or not, constructed on or after the 9th day of`
  line `June, 1955, including premises constructed after the commencement of this Act ^8[but before the`
  line `commencement of the Delhi Rent Control (Amendment) Act, 1988], the annual rent calculated with`
  line `reference to the rent agreed upon between the landlord and the tenant when such premises were first let`
  line `out shall be deemed to be the standard rent for a period of five years from the date of such letting out.`
  line
  line `^8[(c) in the case of any premises, whether residential or not, constructed on or after the`
  line `commencement of the Delhi Rent Control (Amendment) Act, 1988 and to which the provisions of this`
  line `Act are made applicable by virtue of clause (d) of section 3, the rent calculated on the basis of ten per`
  line `cent. per annum of the aggregate amount of the actual cost of construction of the premises and the`
  line `market price of the land comprised in the premises on the date of commencement of the construction,`
  line `of the premises shall be deemed to be the standard rent.]`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section, residential premises include premises let out for the purposes of a`
  line `public hospital, an educational institution, a public library, reading room or an orphanage.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 57 of 1988, s. 3, for "seven and one-half per cent." (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Reasonable" (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Proviso omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 57 of 1988, s. 3, for "seven and one-half per cent." (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Reasonable" (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `6. Proviso omitted by s. 3, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `7. Proviso omitted by s. 3, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (70374)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 7
  title `Revision of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70374&sectionno=6A&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Revision of rent.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the standard rent, or, where`
  line `no standard rent is fixed under the provisions of this Act in respect of any premises, the rent agreed upon`
  line `between the landlord and the tenant, may be increased by ten per cent. every three years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (70376)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Notice of increase of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70376&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a landlord wishes to increase the rent of any premises, he`
  line `shall give the tenant notice of his intention to make the increase and in so far as such increase is lawful`
  line `under this Act, it shall be due and recoverable only in respect of the period of the tenancy after the expiry`
  line `of thirty days from the date on which the notice is given.`
  line `(2) Every notice under sub-section (1) shall be in writing signed by or on behalf of the landlord and`
  line `given in the manner provided in section 106 of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (70377)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Controller to fix standard rent, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 57 of 1988, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70377&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Controller shall, on an application made to him in`
  line `this behalf, either by the landlord or by the tenant, in the prescribed manner, fix in respect of any`
  line premises--
  line
  line `(i) the standard rent referred to in section 6; or`
  line
  line `(ii) the increase, if any, referred to in section 7.`
  line
  line `(2) In fixing the standard rent of any premises of the lawful increase thereof, the Controller shall fix an`
  line `amount which appears to him to be reasonable having regard to the provisions of section 6 or section 7 and`
  line `the circumstances of the case:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that in working out the cost of construction of any premises or the market price of the land`
  line `comprised in such premises for the purposes of section 6, or the cost of improvement, addition or alteration`
  line `referred to in section 7, the Controller may take the assistance of any valuer approved by the Central`
  line `Government in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed and the assessment shall be made by such`
  line `valuer in the manner prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(3) In fixing the standard rent of any premises part of which has been lawfully sub-let, the Controller`
  line `may also fix the standard rent of the part sub-let.`
  line
  line `(4) Where for any reason it is not possible to determine the standard rent of any premises on the`
  line `principles set forth under section 6, the Controller may fix such rent as would be reasonable having regard`
  line `to the situation, locality and condition of the premises and the amenities provided therein and where there`
  line `are similar or nearly similar premises in the locality, having regard also to the standard rent payable in`
  line `respect of such premises.`
  line
  line `(5) The standard rent shall in all cases be fixed for a tenancy of twelve months:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any premises are let or re-let for a period of less than twelve months, the standard`
  line `rent for such tenancy shall bear the same proportion to the annual standard rent as the period of tenancy`
  line `bears to twelve months.`
  line
  line `(6) In fixing the standard rent of any premises under this section, the Controller shall fix the standard`
  line `rent thereof in an unfurnished state and may also determine an additional charge to be payable on account`
  line `of any fittings or furniture supplied by the landlord and it shall be lawful for the landlord to recover such`
  line `additional charge from the tenant.`
  line
  line `(7) In fixing the standard rent of any premises under this section, the Controller shall specify a date`
  line `from which the standard rent so fixed shall be deemed to have effect:`
  line
  line `Provided that in no case the date so specified shall be earlier than one year prior to the date of the filing`
  line `of the application for the fixation of the standard rent.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (70378)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Fixation of interim rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70378&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `No collector of rent or middleman shall be liable to pay`
  line `to his principal, in respect of any premises, any sum by way of rental charges which exceeds, the amount`
  line `which he is entitled under this Act to realise from the tenant or tenants of the premises.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (70379)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Limitation of liability of middlemen.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70379&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Any landlord or tenant may file an`
  line `application to the Controller for fixing the standard rent of the premises or for determining the lawful`
  line `increase of such rent,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of any premises which were let, or in which the cause of action for lawful increase of`
  line `rent arose, before the commencement of this Act, within two years from such commencement;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any premises let after the commencement of this Act ^1[but before the commencement`
  line `of the Delhi Rent Control (Amendment) Act, 1988],--`
  line
  line `(i) where the application is made by the landlord, within two years from the date on which the`
  line `premises were let to the tenant against whom the application is made;`
  line
  line `(ii) where the application is made by the tenant, within two years from the date on which the`
  line `premises were let to that tenant; ^2[and]`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of any premises in which the cause of action of lawful increase of rent arises after the`
  line `commencement of this Act within two years from the date on which the cause of action arises; ^2[and]`
  line
  line `^1[(d) in the case of any premises referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 6, within two`
  line `years from the date of such application:]`
  line
  line `Provided that the Controller may entertain the application after the expiry of the said period of two`
  line `years, if he is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the application in`
  line time.
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 57 of 1988, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (d) has been ins. by s. 7 ibid. As a result of this insertion the word "and" of the end of sub-clause (ii) of clause (b)`
  line `ought to have been omitted and added at the end of clause (c), which has been done by Act 57 of 1988. The irregularity has`
  line `set right. (Ed.)`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (70380)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Limitation for application for fixation of standard rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70380&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Where any sum or other`
  line `consideration has been paid, whether before or after the commencement of this Act, by or on behalf of a`
  line `tenant to a landlord, in contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or of the Delhi and Ajmer Rent`
  line `Control Act, 1952 (38 of 1952), the Controller may, on an application made to him within a period of one`
  line `year from the date of such payment, order the landlord to refund such sum or the value of such consideration`
  line `to the tenant or order adjustment of such sum or the value of such consideration against the rent payable by`
  line `the tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (70381)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Refund of rent, premium, etc., not recoverable under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70381&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Where any sum or other`
  line `consideration has been paid, whether before or after the commencement of this Act, by or on behalf of a`
  line `tenant to a landlord, in contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or of the Delhi and Ajmer Rent`
  line `Control Act, 1952 (38 of 1952), the Controller may, on an application made to him within a period of one`
  line `year from the date of such payment, order the landlord to refund such sum or the value of such consideration`
  line `to the tenant or order adjustment of such sum or the value of such consideration against the rent payable by`
  line `the tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (70382)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Protection of tenant against eviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70382&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in`
  line `any other law or contract, no order or decree for the recovery of possession of any premises shall be made`
  line `by any court or Controller in favour of the landlord against a tenant:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Controller may, on an application made to him in the prescribed manner, make an`
  line `order for the recovery of possession of the premises on one or more of the following grounds only,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the tenant has neither paid nor tendered the whole of the arrears of the rent legally`
  line `recoverable from him within two months of the date on which a notice of demand for the arrears of rent`
  line `has been served of him by the landlord in the manner provided in section 106 of the Transfer of Property`
  line `Act, 1882 (4 of 1882);`
  line
  line `(b) that the tenant has, on or after the 9th day of June, 1952, sub-let, assigned or otherwise parted`
  line `with the possession of the whole or any part of the premises without obtaining the consent in writing`
  line `of the landlord;`
  line
  line `(c) that the tenant has used the premises for a purpose other than that for which they were let--`
  line
  line `(i) if the premises have been let on or after the 9th day of June, 1952, without obtaining the`
  line `consent in writing of the landlord; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if the premises have been let before the said date without obtaining his consent;`
  line
  line `(d) that the premises were let for use as a residence and neither the tenant nor any member of his`
  line `family has been residing therein for a period of six months immediately before the date of the filing of`
  line `the application for the recovery of possession thereof;`
  line
  line `(e) that the premises let for residential purposes are required bona fide by the landlord for`
  line `occupation as a residence for himself or for any member of his family dependent on him, if he is the`
  line `owner thereof, or for any person for whose benefit the premises are held and that the landlord or such`
  line `person has no other reasonably suitable residential accommodation;`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, "premises let for residential purposes" include any`
  line `premises which having been let for use as a residence are, without the consent of the landlord, used`
  line `incidentally for commercial or other purposes;`
  line
  line `(f) that the premises have become unsafe or unfit for human habitation and are required bona fide`
  line `by the landlord for carrying out repairs which cannot be carried out without the premises being vacated;`
  line
  line `(g) that the premises are required bona fide by the landlord for the purpose of building or re-building`
  line `or making thereto any substantial additions or alterations and that such building or re-building or`
  line `addition or alteration cannot be carried out without the premises being vacated;`
  line
  line `(h) that the tenant has, whether before or after the commencement of this Act, ^1***, acquired vacant`
  line `possession of, or been allotted, a residence;`
  line
  line `^1[(hh) that the tenant has, after the commencement of the Delhi Rent Control (Amendment) Act,`
  line `1988, built a residence and ten years have elapsed thereafter;]`
  line
  line `(i) that the premises were let to the tenant for use as a residence by reason of his being in the service`
  line `or employment of the landlord, and that the tenant has ceased, whether before or after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, to be in such service or employment;`
  line
  line `(j) that the tenant has, whether before or after the commencement of this Act, caused or permitted`
  line `to be caused substantial damage to the premises;`
  line
  line `(k) that the tenant has, notwithstanding previous notice, used or dealt with the premises in a manner`
  line `contrary to any condition imposed on the landlord by the Government or the Delhi Development`
  line `Authority or the Municipal Corporation of Delhi while giving him a lease of the land on which the`
  line `premises are situate;`
  line
  line `(l) that the landlord requires the premises in order to carry out any building work at the instance of`
  line `the Government or the Delhi Development Authority or the Municipal Corporation of Delhi is`
  line `pursuance of any improvement scheme or development scheme and that such building work cannot be`
  line `carried out without the premises being vacated.`
  line
  line `(2) No order for the recovery of possession of any premises shall be made on the ground specified in`
  line `clause (a) of the proviso to sub-section (1), if the tenant makes payment or deposit as required by`
  line `section 15;`
  line
  line `Provided that no tenant shall be entitled to the benefit under this sub-section, if, having obtained such`
  line `benefit once in respect of any premises, he again makes a default in the payment of rent of those premises`
  line `for three consecutive months.`
  line
  line `(3) No order for the recovery of possession in any proceeding under sub-section (1) shall be binding on`
  line `any sub-tenant referred to in section 17 who has given notice of his sub-tenancy to the landlord under the`
  line `provisions of that section, unless the sub-tenant is made a party to the proceeding and the order for eviction`
  line `is made binding on him.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of clause (b) of the proviso to sub-section (1), any premises which have been let`
  line `for being used for the purposes of business or profession shall be deemed to have been sub-let by the tenant,`
  line `if the Controller is satisfied that the tenant without obtaining the consent in writing of the landlord has, after`
  line `the 16th day of August, 1958, allowed any person to occupy the whole or any part of the premises ostensibly`
  line `on the ground that such person is a partner of the tenant in the business or profession but really for the`
  line `purpose of sub-letting such premises to that person.`
  line
  line `(5) No application for the recovery of possession of any premises shall lie under sub-section (1) on the`
  line `ground specified in clause (c) of the proviso thereto, unless the landlord has given to the tenant a notice in`
  line `the prescribed manner requiring him to stop the misuse of the premises and the tenant has refused or failed`
  line `to comply with such requirement within one month of the date of service of the notice; and no order for`
  line `eviction against the tenant shall be made in such a case, unless the Controller is satisfied that the misuse of`
  line `the premises is of such a nature that it is a public nuisance or that it causes damage to the premises or is`
  line `otherwise detrimental to the interest of the landlord.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a landlord has acquired any premises by transfer, no application for the recovery of`
  line `possession of such premises shall lie under sub-section (1) on the ground specified in clause (e) of the`
  line `proviso thereto, unless a period of five years have elapsed from the date of the acquisition.`
  line
  line `(7) Where an order for the recovery of possession of any premises is made on the ground specified in`
  line `clause (e) of the proviso to sub-section (1), the landlord shall not be entitled to obtain possession thereof`
  line `before the expiration of a period of six months from the date of the order.`
  line
  line `(8) No order for the recovery of possession of any premises shall be made on the ground specified in`
  line `clause (g) of the proviso to sub-section (1), unless the Controller is satisfied that the proposed reconstruction`
  line `will not radically alter the purpose for which the premises were let or that such radical alteration is in the`
  line `public interest, and that the plans and estimates of such reconstruction have been properly prepared and that`
  line `necessary fund for the purpose are available with the landlord.`
  line
  line `(9) No order for the recovery of possession of any premises shall be made on the ground specified in`
  line `clause (i) of the proviso to sub-section (1), if the Controller is of opinion that there is any bona fide dispute`
  line `as to whether the tenant has ceased to be in the service or employment of the landlord.`
  line
  line `(10) No order for the recovery of possession of any premises shall be made on the ground specified in`
  line `clause (j) of the proviso to sub-section (1), if the tenant, within such time as may be specified in this behalf`
  line `by the Controller, carries out repairs to the damage caused to the satisfaction of the Controller or pays to`
  line `the landlord such amount by way of compensation as the Controller may direct.`
  line
  line `(11) No order for the recovery of possession of any premises shall be made on the ground specified in`
  line `clause (k) of the proviso to sub-section (1), if the tenant, within such time as may be specified in this behalf`
  line `by the Controller, complies with the condition imposed on the landlord by any of the authorities referred to`
  line `in that clause or pays to that authority such amount by way of compensation as the Controller may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "built" omitted by Act 57 of 1988, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (70383)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 16
  title `Right to recover immediate possession of premises to accrue to certain persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 1976, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-12-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70383&sectionno=14A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[14A. Right to recover immediate possession of premises to accrue to certain persons.--`
  line `(1)`
  line `Where a landlord who, being a person in occupation of any residential premises allotted to him by the`
  line `Central Government or any local authority is required, by, or in pursuance of, any general or special order`
  line `made by that Government or authority, to vacate such residential accommodation, or in default, to incur`
  line `certain obligations, on the ground that he owns, in the Union territory of Delhi, a residential accommodation`
  line `either in his own name or in the name of his wife or dependent child, there shall accrue, on and from the date of such order, to such landlord, notwithstanding anything contained elsewhere in this Act or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force or in any contract (whether express or implied), custom or usage to the`
  line `contrary, a right to recover immediately possession of any premises let out by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be construed as conferring a right on a landlord owning, in`
  line `the Union territory of Delhi, two or more dwelling houses whether in his own name or in the name of his`
  line `wife or dependent child to recover the possession of more than one dwelling house and it shall be lawful`
  line `for such landlord to indicate the dwelling house, possession of which he intends to recover.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained elsewhere in this Act or in any there law for the time being in`
  line `force or in any contract, custom or usage to the contrary, where the landlord exercises the right of recovery`
  line `conferred on him by sub-section (1), no compensation shall be payable by him to the tenant or any person`
  line `claiming through or under him and no claim for such compensation shall be entertained by any court,`
  line `tribunal or other authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the landlord had received,--`
  line
  line `(a) any rent in advance from the tenant, he shall, within a period of ninety days from the date of`
  line `recovery of possession of the premises by him, refund to the tenant such amount as represent the rent`
  line `payable for the unexpired portion of the contract, agreement or lease;`
  line
  line `(b) any other payment, he shall, within the period aforesaid, refund to the tenant a sum which shall`
  line `bear the same proportion to the total amount so received, as the unexpired portion of the contract or`
  line `agreement, or lease bears to the total period of contract or agreement or lease:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, if any default is made in making any refund as aforesaid, the landlord shall be`
  line `liable to pay simple interest at the rate of six per cent per annum on the amount which he has omitted or`
  line `failed to refund.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_b:
  sectionId (70384)
  sectionNo 14B
  orderNo 17
  title `Right to recover immediate possession of premises to accrue to members of the armed forces, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 57 of 1988, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70384&sectionno=14B&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_14_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[14B. Right to recover immediate possession of premises to accrue to members of the armed`
  line `forces, etc.-- (1) Where the landlord--`
  line
  line `(a) is a released or retired person from any armed forces and the premises let out by him are required`
  line `for his own residence; or`
  line
  line `(b) is a dependent of a member of any armed forces who had been killed in action and the premises`
  line `let out by such member are required for the residence of the family of such member,`
  line `such person or, as the case may be, the dependent may, within one year from the date of his release or`
  line `retirement from such armed forces or, as the case may be, the date of death of such member, or within a`
  line `period of one year from the date of commencement of the Delhi Rent Control (Amendment) Act, 1988,`
  line `whichever is later, apply to the Controller for recovering the immediate possession of such premises.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the landlord is a member of any of the armed forces and has a period of less than one year`
  line `preceding the date of his retirement and the premises let out by him are required for his own residence after`
  line `his retirement, he may, at any time, within a period of one year before the date of his retirement, apply to`
  line `the Controller for recovering the immediate possession of such premises.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the landlord referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) has let out more than one`
  line `premises, it shall be open to him to make an application under that sub-section in respect of only one of the`
  line `premises chosen by him.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "armed forces" means an armed force of the Union`
  line `constituted under an Act of Parliament and includes a member of the police force constituted under`
  line `Section 3 of the Delhi Police Act, 1978 (34 of 1978).]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_c:
  sectionId (70437)
  sectionNo 14C
  orderNo 18
  title `Right to recover immediate possession of premises to accrue to Central Government and Delhi Administration employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 57 of 1988, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70437&sectionno=14C&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_14_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[14C. Right to recover immediate possession of premises to accrue to Central Government and`
  line `Delhi Administration employees.--(1) Where the landlord is a retired employee of the Central`
  line `Government or of the Delhi Administration, and the premises let out by him are required for his own`
  line `residence, such employee may, within one year from the date of his retirement or within a period of one year from the date of commencement of the Delhi Rent Control (Amendment) Act, 1988, whichever is`
  line `later, apply to the Controller for recovering the immediate possession of such premises.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the landlord is an employee of the Central Government or of the Delhi Administration and`
  line `has a period of less than one year preceding the date of his retirement and the premises let out by him are`
  line `required by him for his own residence after his retirement, he may, at any time within a period of one year`
  line `before the date of his retirement, apply to the Controller for recovering the immediate possession of such`
  line premises.
  line
  line `(3) Where the landlord referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) has let out more than one`
  line `premises, it shall be open to him to make an application under that sub-section in respect of only one of the`
  line `premises chosen by him].`
obj_root_law_sections_14_d:
  sectionId (70386)
  sectionNo 14D
  orderNo 19
  title `Right to recover immediate possession of premises to accrue to a widow.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 57 of 1988, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70386&sectionno=14D&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_14_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[14D. Right to recover immediate possession of premises to accrue to a widow.-- (1) Where the`
  line `landlord is a widow and the premises let out by her, or by her husband, are required by her for her own`
  line `residence, she may apply to the Controller for recovering the immediate possession of such premises.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the landlord referred to in sub-section (1) has let out more than one premises, it shall he open`
  line `to her to make an application under that sub-section in respect of any one of the premises chosen by her.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (70387)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 20
  title `When a tenant can get the benefit of protection against eviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70387&sectionno=15&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) In every proceeding of`
  line `the recovery of possession of any premises on the ground specified in clause (a) of the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 14, the Controller shall, after giving the parties an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `make an order directing the tenant to pay to the landlord or deposit with the Controller within one month`
  line `of the date of the order, an amount calculated at the rate of rent at which it was last paid for the period for`
  line `which the arrears of the rent were legally recoverable from the tenant including the period subsequent`
  line `thereto up to the end of the month previous to that in which payment or deposit is made and to continue to`
  line `pay or deposit, month by month, by the fifteenth of each succeeding month, a sum equivalent to the rent at`
  line `that rate.`
  line
  line `(2) If, in any proceeding for the recovery of possession of any premises on any ground other than that`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1), the tenant contests the claim for eviction, the landlord may, at any stage of`
  line `the proceeding, make an application to the Controller for an order on the tenant to pay to the landlord the`
  line `amount of rent legally recoverable from the tenant and the Controller may, after giving the parties an`
  line `opportunity of being heard, make an order in accordance with the provisions of the said sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) If, in any proceeding referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), there is any dispute as to the`
  line `amount of rent payable by the tenant, the Controller shall, within fifteen days of the date of the first hearing`
  line `of the proceeding, fix an interim rent in relation to the premises to be paid or deposited in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), as the case may be until the standard rent in relation`
  line `thereto is fixed having regard to the provisions of this Act, and the amount of arrears if any, calculated on`
  line `the basis of the standard rent shall be paid or deposited by the tenant within one month of the date on which`
  line `the standard rent is fixed or such further time as the Controller may allow in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) If, in any proceeding referred to in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), there is any dispute as to the`
  line `person or persons to whom the rent is payable, the Controller may direct the tenant to deposit with the`
  line `Controller the amount payable by him under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), as the`
  line `case may be, and in such a case, no person shall be entitled to withdraw the amount in deposit until the`
  line `Controller decides the dispute and makes an order for payment of the same.`
  line
  line `(5) If the Controller is satisfied that any dispute referred to in sub-section (4) has been raised by a tenant`
  line `for reasons which are false or frivolous, the Controller may order the defence against eviction to be struck`
  line `out and proceed with the hearing of the application.`
  line
  line `(6) If a tenant makes payment or deposit as required by sub-section (1) or sub-section (3), no order shall`
  line `be made for the recovery of possession on the ground of default in the payment of rent by the tenant, but`
  line `the Controller may allow such costs as he may deem fit to the landlord.`
  line
  line `(7) If a tenant fails to make payment or deposit as required by this section, the Controller may order the`
  line `defence against eviction to be struck out and proceed with the hearing of the application.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (70388)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 21
  title `Restrictions on sub-letting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70388&sectionno=16&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where at any time before the 9th day of June, 1952, a tenant has`
  line `sub-let the whole or any part of the premises and the sub-tenant is, at the commencement of this Act, in`
  line `occupation of such premises, then, notwithstanding that the consent of the landlord was not obtained for`
  line `such sub-letting, the premises shall be deemed to have been lawfully sub-let.`
  line
  line `(2) No premises which have been sub-let either in whole or in part on or after the 9th day of June, 1952,`
  line `without obtaining the consent in writing of the landlord, shall be deemed to have been lawfully sub-let.`
  line `(3) After the commencement of this Act, no tenant shall, without the previous consent in writing of the`
  line landlord,--
  line
  line `(a) sub-let the whole or any part of the premises held by him as a tenant; or`
  line
  line `(b) transfer or assign his rights in the tenancy or in any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(4) No landlord shall claim or receive the payment of any sum as premium or pugree or claim or receive`
  line `any consideration whatsoever in cash or in kind for giving his consent to the sub-letting of the whole or any`
  line `part of the premises held by the tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (70389)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 22
  title `Notice of creation and termination of sub-tenancy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70389&sectionno=17&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, after the commencement of this`
  line `Act, any premises are sub-let either in whole or in part by the tenant with the previous consent in writing`
  line `of the landlord, the tenant or the sub-tenant to whom the premises are sub-let may, in the prescribed manner,`
  line `give notice to the landlord of the creation of the sub-tenancy within one month of the date of such`
  line `sub-letting and notify the termination of such sub-tenancy within one month of such termination.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, before the commencement of this Act, any premises have been lawfully sub-let either in`
  line `whole or in part by the tenant, the tenant or the sub-tenant to whom the premises have been sub-let may, in`
  line `the prescribed manner, give notice to the landlord of the creation of the sub-tenancy within six months of`
  line `the commencement of this Act, and notify the termination of such sub-tenancy within one month of such`
  line termination.
  line
  line `(3) Where in any case mentioned in sub-section (2), the landlord contests that the premises were not`
  line `lawfully sub-let, and an application is made to the Controller in this behalf, either by the landlord or by the`
  line `sub-tenant, within two months of the date of the receipt of the notice of sub-letting by the landlord or the`
  line `issue of the notice by the tenant or the sub-tenant, as the case may be, the Controller shall decide the dispute.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (70390)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 23
  title `Sub-tenant to be tenant in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70390&sectionno=18&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an order for eviction in respect of any`
  line `premises is made under section 14 against a tenant but not against a sub-tenant referred to in section 17 and`
  line `a notice of the sub-tenancy has been given to the landlord, the sub-tenant shall, with effect from the date of`
  line `the order, be deemed to become a tenant holding directly under the landlord in respect of the premises in`
  line `his occupation on the same terms and conditions on which the tenant would have held from the landlord, if`
  line `the tenancy had continued.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, before the commencement of this Act, the interest of a tenant in respect of any premises has`
  line `been determined without determining the interest of any sub-tenant to whom the premises either in whole`
  line `or in part had been lawfully sub-let, the sub-tenant shall, with effect from the date of the commencement`
  line `of this Act, be deemed to have become a tenant holding directly under the landlord on the same terms and`
  line `conditions on which the tenant would have held from the landlord, if the tenancy had continued.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (70391)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 24
  title `Recovery of possession for occupation and re-entry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 57 of 1988, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70391&sectionno=19&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a landlord recovers possession`
  line `of any premises from the tenant in pursuance of an order made under clause (e) of the proviso to`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 14 ^1[or under sections 14A, 14B, I4C, 14D and 21, the landlord shall not, except`
  line `with the permission of the Controller obtained in the prescribed manner, re-let the whole or any part of the`
  line `premises within three years from the date of obtaining such possession, and in granting such permission,`
  line `the Controller may direct the landlord to put such evicted tenant in possession of the premises.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a landlord recovers possession of any premises as aforesaid and the premises are not`
  line `occupied by the landlord or by the person for whose benefit the premises are held, within two months of`
  line `obtaining such possession, or the premises having been so occupied are, at any time within three years from the date of obtaining possession, re-let to any person other than the evicted tenant without obtaining the`
  line `permission of the Controller under sub-section (1) or the possession of such premises is transferred to`
  line `another person for reasons which do not appear to the Controller to be bona fide, the Controller may, on an`
  line `application made to him in this behalf by such evicted tenant within such time as may be prescribed, direct`
  line `the landlord to put the tenant in possession of the premises or to pay him such compensation as the`
  line `Controller thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (70392)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 25
  title `Recovery of possession for repairs and re-building and re-entry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70392&sectionno=20&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) In making any order on`
  line `the grounds specified in clause (f) or clause (g) of the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 14, the Controller`
  line `shall ascertain from the tenant whether he elects to be placed in occupation of the premises or part thereof`
  line `from which he is to be evicted and if the tenant so elects, shall record the fact of the election in the order`
  line `and specify therein the date on or before which he shall deliver possession so as to enable the landlord to`
  line `commence the work of repairs or building or re-building, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) If the tenant delivers possession on or before the date specified in the order, the landlord shall, on`
  line `the completion of the work of repairs of building or re-building, place the tenant in occupation of the`
  line `premises or part thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) If, after the tenant has delivered possession on or before the date specified in the order, the landlord`
  line `fails to commence the work of repairs or building or re-building within one month of the specified date or`
  line `fails to complete the work in a reasonable time or having completed the work, fails to place the tenant in`
  line `occupation of the premises in accordance with sub-section (2), the Controller may, on an application made`
  line `to him in this behalf by the tenant within such time as may be prescribed, order the landlord to place the`
  line `tenant in occupation of the premises or part thereof or to pay to the tenant such compensation as the`
  line `Controller thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (70393)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 26
  title `Recovery of possession in case of tenancies for limited period.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70393&sectionno=21&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Where a landlord does`
  line `not require the whole or any part of any premises for a particular period, and the landlord, after obtaining`
  line `the permission of the Controller in the prescribed manner, lets the whole of the premises or part thereof as`
  line `a residence for such period as may be agreed to in writing between the landlord and the tenant and the`
  line `tenant does not on the expiry of the said period, vacate such premises, then, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 14 or in any other law, the Controller may, on an application made to him in this behalf`
  line `by the landlord within such time as may be prescribed, place the landlord in vacant possession of the`
  line `premises or part thereof by evicting the tenant and every other person who may be in occupation of such`
  line premises.
  line
  line `^2](2) While making an order under sub-section (1), the Controller may award to the landlord such`
  line `damages for the use or occupation of the premises at such rates as he considers proper in the circumstances`
  line `of the case for the period from the date of such order till the date of actual vacation by the tenant.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 21 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 57 of 1988, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (70394)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 27
  title `Special provision for recovery of possession in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Added by Act 57 of 1988, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70394&sectionno=22&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Where the landlord in respect of`
  line `any premises is any company or other body corporate or any local authority or any public institution and`
  line `the premises are required for the use of employees of such landlord or in the case of a public institution, for`
  line `the furtherance of its activities, then, notwithstanding anything contained in section 14 or any other law,`
  line `the Controller may, on an application made to him in this behalf by such landlord, place the landlord in`
  line `vacant possession of such premises by evicting the tenant and every other person who may be in occupation`
  line `thereof, if the Controller is satisfied--`
  line
  line `(a) that the tenant to whom such premises were let for use as a residence at a time when he was in`
  line `the service or employment of the landlord, has ceased to be in such service or employment; or`
  line
  line `(b) that the tenant has acted in contravention of the terms, express or implied, under which he was`
  line `authorised to occupy such premises; or`
  line
  line `(c) that any other person is in unauthorised occupation of such premises; or`
  line
  line `(d) that the premises are required bona fide by the public institution for the furtherance of its`
  line activities.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "public institution" includes any educational institution,`
  line `library, hospital and charitable dispensary ^1[but does not include any such institution set up by any private`
  line trust].
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (70395)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 28
  title `Permission to construct additional structures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70395&sectionno=23&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Where the landlord proposes to make any`
  line `improvement in, or construct any additional structure on, any building which has been let to a tenant and`
  line `the tenant refuses to allow the landlord to make such improvement or construct such additional structure`
  line `and the Controller, on an application made to him in this behalf by the landlord, is satisfied that the landlord`
  line `is ready and willing to commence the work and that such work will not cause any undue hardship to the`
  line `tenant, the Controller may permit the landlord to do such work and may make such other order as he thinks`
  line `fit in the circumstances of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (70396)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 29
  title `Special provision regarding vacant building sites.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70396&sectionno=24&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 14, where any premises which have been let comprise vacant land upon which it is permissible`
  line `under the building regulations or municipal bye-laws, for the time being in force, to erect any building,`
  line `whether for use as a residence or for any other purpose and the landlord proposing to erect such building is`
  line `unable to obtain possession of the land from the tenant by agreement with him and the Controller, on an`
  line `application made to him in this behalf by the landlord, is satisfied that the landlord is ready and willing to`
  line `commence the work and that the severance of the vacant land from the rest of the premises will not cause`
  line `undue hardship to the tenant, the Controller may--`
  line
  line `(a) direct such severance;`
  line
  line `(b) place the landlord in possession of the vacant land;`
  line
  line `(c) determine the rent payable by the tenant in respect of the rest of the premises; and`
  line
  line `(d) make such other order as he thinks fit in the circumstances of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (70397)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 30
  title `Vacant possession to landlord.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70397&sectionno=25&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, where the`
  line `interest of a tenant in any premises is determined for any reason whatsoever and any order is made by the`
  line `Controller under this Act for the recovery of possession of such premises the order shall, subject to the`
  line `provisions of section 18, be binding on all persons who may be in occupation of the premises and vacant`
  line `possession thereof shall be given to the landlord by evicting all such person therefrom:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall apply to any persons who has an independent title to such`
  line premises.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25_a:
  sectionId (70398)
  sectionNo 25A
  orderNo 31
  title `Provisions of this chapter to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content
  footnotes `2. Chapter IIIA (consisting of sections 25A to 25C ins. by Act 18 of 1976, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-12-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70398&sectionno=25A&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[25A. Provisions of this Chapter to have overriding effect.--The provisions of this Chapter or any`
  line `rule made thereunder shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained elsewhere`
  line `in this Act or in any other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_b:
  sectionId (70436)
  sectionNo 25B
  orderNo 32
  title `Special procedure for the disposal of applications for eviction on the ground of bona fide requirement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70436&sectionno=25B&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_25_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[25B. Special procedure for the disposal of applications for eviction on the ground of bona fide`
  line requirement.--
  line
  line `(1) Every application by a landlord for the recovery of possession of any premises on the ground`
  line `specified in clause (e) of the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 14, or under section 14A`
  line `^2[or under section`
  line `14B or under section I4C or under section 14D], shall be dealt with in accordance with the procedure`
  line `specified in this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The Controller shall issue summons, in relation to every application referred to in sub-section (1),`
  line `in the form specified in the Third Schedule.`
  line
  line `(3) (a) The Controller shall, in addition to, and simultaneously with, the issue of summons for service`
  line `on the tenant, also direct the summons to be served by registered post, acknowledgment due, addressed to`
  line `the tenant or his agent empowered to accept the service at the place where the tenant or his agent actually`
  line `and voluntarily resides or carries on business or personally works for gain and may, if the circumstances of`
  line `the case so require, also direct the publication of the summons in a newspaper circulating in the locality in`
  line `which the tenant is last known to have resided or carried on business or personally worked for gain.`
  line
  line `(b) When an acknowledgement purporting to be signed by the tenant or his agent is received by the`
  line `Controller or the registered article containing the summons is received back with an endorsement purporting`
  line `to have been made by a postal employee to the effect that the tenant or his agent had refused to take delivery`
  line `of the registered article, the Controller may declare that there has been a valid service of summons.`
  line
  line `(4) The tenant on whom the summons is duly served (whether in the ordinary way or by registered post)`
  line `in the form specified in the Third Schedule shall not contest the prayer for eviction from the premises unless`
  line `he files an affidavit stating the grounds on which he seeks to contest the application for eviction and obtains`
  line `leave from the Controller as hereinafter provided; and in default of his appearance in pursuance of the`
  line `summons or his obtaining such leave, the statement made by the landlord in the application for eviction`
  line `shall be deemed to be admitted by the tenant and the applicant shall be entitled to an order for eviction on`
  line `the ground aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(5) The Controller shall give to the tenant leave to contest the application if the affidavit filed by the`
  line `tenant discloses such facts as would disentitle the landlord from obtaining an order for the recovery of`
  line `possession of the premises on the ground specified in clause (c) of the proviso to sub-section (1) of section`
  line `14, or under section 14A.`
  line
  line `(6) Where leave is granted to the tenant to contest the application, the Controller shall commence the`
  line `hearing of the application as early as practicable.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) of section 37, the Controller shall, while`
  line `holding an inquiry in a proceeding to which this Chapter applies, follow the practice and procedure of a`
  line `Court of Small Causes, including the recording of evidence.`
  line
  line `(8) No appeal or second appeal shall lie against an order for the recovery of possession of any premises`
  line `made by the Controller in accordance with the procedure specified in this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may, for the purpose of satisfying itself that an order made by the`
  line `Controller under this section is according to law, call for the records of the case and pass such order in`
  line `respect thereto as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(9) Where no application has been made to the High Court on revision, the Controller may exercise the`
  line `powers of review in accordance with the provisions of Order XLVII of the First Schedule to the Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `(10) Save as otherwise provided in this Chapter, the procedure for the disposal of an application for`
  line `eviction on the ground specified in clause (e) of the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 14, or under section`
  line `14A, shall be the same as the procedure for the disposal of applications by Controllers.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Chapter IIIA (consisting of sections 25A to 25C ins. by Act 18 of 1976, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-12-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 57 of 1988, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_c:
  sectionId (70400)
  sectionNo 25C
  orderNo 33
  title `Act to have effect in a modified form in relation to certain persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_c_content
  footnotes `1. Chapter IIIA (consisting of sections 25A to 25C ins. by Act 18 of 1976, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-12-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70400&sectionno=25C&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_25_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[25C. Act to have effect in a modified form in relation to certain persons.--(1) Nothing contained`
  line `in sub-section (6) of section 14 shall apply to a landlord who, being a person in occupation of any residential`
  line `premises allotted to him by the Central Government or any local authority is required by or in pursuance`
  line `of, an order made by that Government or authority to vacate such residential accommodation, or, in default,`
  line `to incur certain obligations, or the ground that he owns a residential accommodation either in his own name`
  line `or in the name of his wife or dependent child in the Union territory of Delhi.`
  line
  line `(2) In the case of a landlord who, being a person of the category specified in sub-section (1), has`
  line `obtained, on the ground specified in clause (e) of the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 14, or under section 14A, an order for the eviction of a tenant from any premises, the provisions of sub-section (7) of`
  line `section 14 shall have effect as if for the words "six months", occurring therein, the words "two months"`
  line `were substituted.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (70401)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 34
  title `Receipt to be given for rent paid.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70401&sectionno=26&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every tenant shall pay rent within the time fixed by contract`
  line `or in the absence of such contract, by the fifteenth day of the month next following the month for which it`
  line `is payable ^1[and where any default occurs in the payment of rent, the tenant shall be liable to pay simple`
  line `interest at the rate of fifteen per cent, per annum from the date on which such payment of rent is due to the`
  line `date on which it is paid.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every tenant who makes a payment of rent to his landlord shall be entitled to obtain forthwith from`
  line `the landlord or his authorised agent a written receipt for the amount paid to him, signed by the landlord or`
  line `his authorised agent:`
  line `^2[Provided that it shall be open to the tenant to remit the rent to his landlord by postal money order.]`
  line
  line `(3) If the landlord or his authorised agent refuses or neglects to deliver to the tenant a receipt referred`
  line `to in sub-section (2), the Controller may, on an application made to him in this behalf by the tenant within`
  line `two months from the date of payment and after hearing the landlord or his authorised agent, by order direct`
  line `the landlord or his authorised agent to pay to the tenant, by way of damages, such sum not exceeding double`
  line `the amount of rent paid by the tenant and the costs of the application and shall also grant a certificate to the`
  line `tenant in respect of the rent paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Added by Act 57 of 1988, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 14, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (70402)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 35
  title `Deposit of rent by the tenant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70402&sectionno=27&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the landlord does not accept any rent tendered by the`
  line `tenant within the time referred to in section 26 of refuses or neglects to deliver a receipt referred to therein`
  line `or where there is a bona fide doubt as to the person or persons to whom the rent is payable, the tenant may`
  line `deposit such rent with the Controller in the prescribed manner:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that in cases where there is a bona fide doubt as to the person or persons to whom the rent`
  line `is payable, the tenant may remit such rent to the Controller by postal money order.]`
  line `(2) The deposit shall be accompanied by an application by the tenant containing the following`
  line `particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the premises for which the rent is deposited with a description sufficient for identifying the`
  line premises;
  line
  line `(b) the period for which the rent is deposited;`
  line
  line `(c) the name and address of the landlord or the person or persons claiming to be entitled to such`
  line rent;
  line
  line `(d) the reasons and circumstances for which the application for depositing the rent is made;`
  line
  line `(e) such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) On such deposit of the rent being made, the Controller shall send in the prescribed manner a copy`
  line `or copies of the application to the landlord or persons claiming to be entitled to the rent with an endorsement`
  line `of the date of the deposit.`
  line
  line `(4) If an application is made for the withdrawal of any deposit of rent, the Controller shall, if satisfied`
  line `that the applicant is the person entitled to receive the rent deposited, order the amount of the rent to be paid`
  line `to him in the manner prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order for payment of any deposit of rent shall be made by the Controller under this`
  line `sub-section without giving all persons named by the tenant in his application under sub-section (2) as claiming to be entitled to payment of such rent an opportunity of being heard and such order shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the rights of such persons to receive such rent being decided by a court of competent`
  line jurisdiction.
  line
  line `(5) If at the time of filing the application under sub-section (4), but not after the expiry of thirty days`
  line `from receiving the notice of deposit, the landlord or the person or persons claiming to be entitled to the rent`
  line `complains or complain to the Controller that the statements in the tenant's application of the reasons and`
  line `circumstances which led him to deposit the rent are untrue, the Controller, after giving the tenant an`
  line `opportunity of being heard, may levy on the tenant a fine which may extend to an amount equal to two`
  line `months’ rent, if the Controller is satisfied that the said statements were materially untrue and may order`
  line `that a sum out of the fine realised be paid to the landlord as compensation.`
  line
  line `(6) The Controller may, on the complaint of the tenant and after giving an opportunity to the landlord`
  line `of being heard, levy on the landlord a fine which may extend to an amount equal to two months' rent, if the`
  line `Controller is satisfied that the landlord, without any reasonable cause, refused to accept rent though tendered`
  line `to him within the time referred to in section 26 and may further order that a sum out of the fine realised be`
  line `paid to the tenant as compensation.`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (70403)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 36
  title `Time limit for making deposit and consequences of incorrect particulars in application for deposit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70403&sectionno=28&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) No rent deposited under section 27 shall be considered to have been validly deposited under`
  line `that section, unless the deposit is made within twenty-one days of the time referred to in section 26 for`
  line `payment of the rent.`
  line
  line `(2) No such deposit shall be considered to have been validly made, if the tenant wilfully makes any`
  line `false statement in his application for depositing the rent, unless the landlord has withdrawn the amount`
  line `deposited before the date of filing an application for the recovery of possession of the premises from the`
  line tenant.
  line
  line `(3) If the rent is deposited within the time mentioned in sub-section (1) and does not cease to be a valid`
  line `deposit for the reason mentioned in sub-section (2), the deposit shall constitute payment of rent to the`
  line `landlord, as if the amount deposited had been validly tendered.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (70404)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 37
  title `Saving as to acceptance of rent and forfeiture of rent in deposit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70404&sectionno=29&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The withdrawal of rent`
  line `deposited under section 27 in the manner provided therein shall not operate as an admission against the`
  line `person withdrawing it of the correctness of the rate of rent, the period of default, the amount due, or of any`
  line `other facts stated in the tenant's application for depositing the rent under the said section.`
  line
  line `(2) Any rent in deposit which is not withdrawn by the landlord or by the person or persons entitled to`
  line `receive such rent shall be forfeited to Government by an order made by the Controller, if it is not withdrawn`
  line `before the expiration of five years from the date of posting of the notice of deposit.`
  line
  line `(3) Before passing an order of forfeiture the Controller shall give notice to the landlord or the person`
  line `or persons entitled to receive the rent in deposit by registered post at the last known address of such landlord`
  line `or person or persons and shall also publish the notice in his office and in any local newspaper.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (70405)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 38
  title `Application of the Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70405&sectionno=30&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Chapter shall apply to all hotels and lodging`
  line `houses in the areas which, immediately before the 7th day of April, 1958, were included in the New Delhi`
  line `Municipal Committee, Municipal Committee, Delhi and the Notified Area Committee, Civil Station, Delhi`
  line `and may be applied by the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, to hotels and lodging`
  line `houses within the limits of such other urban area of the Municipal Corporation of Delhi as may be specified`
  line `in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Central Government is of opinion that it would not be desirable in the public interest`
  line `to make the provisions of this Chapter applicable to any class of hotels or lodging houses, it may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, exempt such class of hotels or lodging houses from the operation of this`
  line Chapter.
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (70406)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 39
  title `Fixing of fair rate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70406&sectionno=31&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Controller, on a written complaint or otherwise, has reason to`
  line `believe that the charges made for board or lodging or any other service provided in any hotel or lodging`
  line `houses are excessive, he may fix a fair rate to be charged for board, lodging or other services provided in`
  line `the hotel or lodging house and in fixing such fair rate, specified separately the rate for lodging, board or`
  line `other services.`
  line
  line `(2) In determining the fair rate under sub-section (1), the Controller shall have regard to the`
  line `circumstances of the case and to the prevailing rate of charges for the same or similar accommodation,`
  line `board and service, during the twelve months immediately preceding the 1st day of June, 1951, and to any`
  line `general increase in the cost of living after that date.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (70407)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 40
  title `Revision of fair rate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70407&sectionno=32&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `On a written application from the manager of a hotel or the owner of a`
  line `lodging house or otherwise, the Controller may, from time to time, revise the fair rate to be charged for`
  line `board, lodging or other service in a hotel or lodging house, and fix such rate as he may deem fit having`
  line `regard to any general rise or fall in the cost of living which may have occurred after the fixing of fair rate.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (70408)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 41
  title `Charges in excess of fair rate not recoverable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70408&sectionno=33&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `When the Controller has determined the fair rate`
  line `of charges in respect of a hotel or lodging house,--`
  line
  line `(a) the manager of the hotel or the owner of the lodging house, as the case may be, shall not charge`
  line `any amount in excess of the fair rate and shall not, except with the previous written permission of the`
  line `Controller, withdraw from the lodger any concession or service allowed at the time when the Controller`
  line `determined the fair rate;`
  line
  line `(b) any agreement for the payment of any charges in excess of such fair rate shall be void in respect`
  line `of such excess and shall be construed as if it were an agreement for payment of the said fair rate;`
  line
  line `(c) any sum paid by a lodger in excess of the fair rate shall be recoverable by him at any time within`
  line `a period of six months from the date of the payment from the manager of the hotel or the owner of the`
  line `lodging house or his legal representatives and may, without prejudice to any other mode of recovery,`
  line `be deducted by such lodger from any amount payable by him to such manager or owner.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (70409)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 42
  title `Recovery of possession by manager of a hotel or the owner of a lodging house.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70409&sectionno=34&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the manager of a hotel or the owner of a lodging house`
  line `shall he entitled to recover possession of the accommodation provided by him to a lodger on obtaining a`
  line `certificate from the Controller certifying--`
  line
  line `(a) that the lodger has been guilty of conduct which is a nuisance or which causes annoyance to`
  line `any adjoining or neighboring ledger;`
  line
  line `Explanation. --For the purposes of this clause, “nuisance” shall be deemed to include any act which`
  line `constitutes an offence under the Suppression of Immoral Traffic in Women and Girls Act, 1956 (104`
  line `of 1956);`
  line
  line `(b) that the accommodation is reasonably and bona fide required by the owner of the hotel or`
  line `lodging house, as the case may be, either for his own occupation or for the occupation of any person`
  line `for whose benefit the accommodation is held, or any other cause which may be deemed satisfactory to`
  line `the Controller;`
  line
  line `(c) that the lodger has failed to vacate the accommodation on the termination of the period of the`
  line `agreement in respect thereof;`
  line
  line `(d) that the lodger has done any act which is inconsistent with the purpose for which the`
  line `accommodation was given to him or which is likely to affect adversely or substantially the owner's`
  line `interest therein;`
  line
  line `(e) that the lodger has failed to pay the rent due from him.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (70410)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 43
  title `Appointment of Controllers and additional Controllers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70410&sectionno=35&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, appoint as many Controllers as it thinks fit, and define the local limits`
  line `within which, or the hotels and lodging houses in respect of which, each Controller shall exercise the powers`
  line `conferred, and perform the duties imposed, on Controllers by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may also, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint as many`
  line `additional Controllers as it thinks fit and an additional Controller shall perform such of the functions of the`
  line `Controller as may, subject to the control of the Central Government, be assigned to him in writing by the`
  line `Controller and in the discharge of these functions, an additional Controller shall have and shall exercise the`
  line `same powers and discharge the same duties as the Controller.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a Controller or an additional Controller, unless`
  line `he has for at least five years held a judicial office in India or has for at least seven years been practising as`
  line `an advocate or a pleader in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (70411)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 44
  title `Powers of Controller.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70411&sectionno=36&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Controller may--`
  line
  line `(a) transfer any proceeding pending before him for disposal to any additional Controller, or`
  line
  line `(b) withdraw any proceeding pending before any additional Controller and dispose it of himself or`
  line `transfer the proceeding for disposal to any other additional Controller.`
  line
  line `(2) The Controller shall have the same powers as are tested in a civil court under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), when trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `and any proceeding before the Controller shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning`
  line `of section 193 and section 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and the Controller shall be deemed`
  line `to be a civil court within the meaning of Section 480 and Section 482 of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1898 (5 of 1898).`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of holding any inquiry or discharging any duty under this Act, the Controller`
  line may,--
  line
  line `(a) after giving not less than twenty-four hours’ notice in writing, enter and inspect or authorise`
  line `any officer subordinate to him to enter and inspect any premises at any time between sunrise and sunset;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) by written order, require any person to produce for his inspection all such accounts, books or`
  line `other documents relevant to the inquiry at such time and at such place as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(4) The Controller may, if he thinks fit, appoint one or more persons having special knowledge of the`
  line `matter under consideration as an assessor or assessors to advise him in the proceeding before him.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (70412)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 45
  title `Procedure to be followed by Controller.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70412&sectionno=37&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) No order which prejudicially affects any person`
  line `shall be made by the Controller under this Act without giving him a reasonable opportunity of showing`
  line `cause against the order proposed to be made and until his objections, if any, and any evidence he may`
  line `produce in support of the same have been considered by the Controller.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any rules that may be made under this Act, the Controller shall, while holding an inquiry`
  line `in any proceeding before him, follow as far as may be the practice and procedure of a Court of Small`
  line `Causes, including the recording of evidence.`
  line
  line `(3) In all proceedings before him, the Controller shall consider the question of costs and award such`
  line `costs to or against any party as the Controller considers reasonable.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (70413)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 46
  title `Appeal to the Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 57 of 1988, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70413&sectionno=38&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) An appeal shall lie from every order of the Controller made under`
  line `this Act ^1[only on questions of law] to the Rent Control Tribunal hereinafter referred to as the Tribunal)`
  line `consisting of one person only to be appointed by the Central Government by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that no appeal shall lie from an order of the Controller made under section 21.]`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal under sub-section (1) shall be preferred within thirty days from the date of the order made`
  line `by the Controller:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty days, if`
  line `it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in time.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal shall have all the power vested in a court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5`
  line `of 1908), when hearing an appeal.`
  line
  line `(4) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (3), the Tribunal may, on an application made to`
  line `it or otherwise, by order transfer any proceeding pending before any Controller or additional Controller to`
  line `another Controller or additional Controller and the Controller or additional Controller to whom the`
  line `proceeding is so transferred may, subject to any special directions in the order of transfer, dispose of the`
  line proceeding.
  line
  line `(5) A person shall not be qualified for appointment to the Tribunal, unless he is, or has been, a district`
  line `judge or has for at least ten years held a judicial office in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_a:
  sectionId (70414)
  sectionNo 38A
  orderNo 47
  title `Additional Rent Control Tribunals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70414&sectionno=38A&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_38_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[38A. Additional Rent Control Tribunals.--1) For the expeditious disposal of appeals and`
  line `applications under section 38, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `constitute as many Additional Rent Control Tribunals as it deems fit and appoint to each such Additional`
  line `Rent Control Tribunal (hereinafter referred to as the Additional Tribunal) one person qualified for`
  line `appointment to the Tribunal in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (5) of that section.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 38, the Tribunal may, by order in writing,--`
  line
  line `(a) specify the appeals or classes of appeals under sub-section (1) of that section which may be`
  line `preferred to and disposed of by each Additional Tribunal and the classes of cases in which each`
  line `Additional Tribunal may exercise the powers of the Tribunal under sub-section (4) of that section;`
  line
  line `(b) transfer any appeal or proceeding pending before it for disposal to any Additional Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(c) withdraw any appeal or proceeding pending before any Additional Tribunal and dispose it of`
  line `itself or transfer the appeal or proceeding for disposal to any other Additional Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3) of section 38 shall apply in relation to an Additional`
  line `Tribunal as they apply in relation to the Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38_b:
  sectionId (70415)
  sectionNo 38B
  orderNo 48
  title `Power of High Court to transfer appeals, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 2, Act 37 of 1984.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70415&sectionno=38B&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_38_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[38B. Power of High Court to transfer appeals, etc.--The High Court may also, on an application`
  line `made to it or otherwise, by order, transfer--`
  line
  line `(a) any appeal or proceeding pending before the Tribunal to any Additional Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(b) any appeal or proceeding pending before any Additional Tribunal to the Tribunal or in any other`
  line `Additional Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (70416)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 49
  title [Omitted.].
  content `[Second appeal.]--Omitted by The Delhi Rent Control (Amendment) Act, 1988 (57 of 1988), s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-12-1988)`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70416&sectionno=39&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (70417)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 50
  title `Amendment of orders.`
  content `Clerical or arithmetical mistakes in any order passed by a Controller or 1the Tribunal or an Additional Tribunal or errors arising therein from any accidental slip or omission may, at any time, be corrected by the Controller or ^1[the Tribunal on an Additional Tribunal] on an application received in this behalf from any of the parties or otherwise.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70417&sectionno=40&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (70418)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 51
  title `Controller to exercise powers of a magistrate for recovery of fine.`
  content `Any fine imposed by a Controller under this Act shall be paid by the person fined within such time as may be allowed by the Controller and the Controller may, for good and sufficient reason, extend the time, and in default of such payment, the amount shall be recoverable as a fine under the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898, (5 of 1898) and the Controller shall be deemed to be a magistrate under the said Code for the purposes of such recovery.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70418&sectionno=41&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (70419)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 52
  title `Controller to exercise powers of civil court for execution of other orders.`
  content `Save as otherwise provided in section 41, an order made by the Controller or an order passed on appeal under this Act shall be executable by the Controller as a decree of a civil court and for this purpose, the Controller shall have all the powers of a civil court.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70419&sectionno=42&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (70420)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 53
  title `Finality of order.`
  content `Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, every order made by the Controller or an order passed on appeal under this Act shall be final and shall not be called in question in any original suit, application or execution proceeding.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70420&sectionno=43&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (70421)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 54
  title `Landlord’s duty to keep the premises in good repair.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70421&sectionno=44&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every landlord shall be bound to keep the premises in good and tenantable repairs.`
  line
  line `(2) If the landlord neglects or fails to make, within a reasonable time after notice in writing, any repairs which he is bound to make under sub-section (1) the tenant may make the same himself and deduct the expenses of such repairs from the rent or otherwise recover them from the landlord:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount so deducted or recoverable in any year shall not exceed one-twelfth of the rent payable by the tenant for that year.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any repairs without which the premises are not habitable or usable except with undue inconvenience are to be made and the landlord neglects or fails to make them after notice in writing, the tenant may apply to the Controller for permission to make such repairs himself and may submit to the Controller an estimate of the cost of such repairs, and, thereupon, the Controller may, after giving the landlord an opportunity of being heard and after considering such estimate of the cost and making such inquiries as he may consider necessary, by an order in writing, permit the tenant to make such repairs at such cost as may be specified in the order and it shall thereafter be lawful for the tenant to make such repairs himself and to deduct the cost thereof, which shall in no case exceed the amount so specified, from the rent or otherwise recover it from the landlord:`
  line
  line `Provided that the amount so deducted or recoverable in any year shall not exceed one-half of the rent payable by the tenant for that year:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if any repairs not covered by the said amount are necessary in the opinion of the Controller, and the tenant agrees to bear the excess cost himself, the Controller may permit the tenant to make such repairs.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (70422)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 55
  title `Cutting off or withholding essential supply or service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70422&sectionno=45&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) No landlord either himself or through any person purporting to act on his behalf shall without just and sufficient cause cut off or withhold any essential supply or service enjoyed by the tenant in respect of the premises let to him.`
  line
  line `(2) If a landlord contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1), the tenant may make an application to the Controller complaining of such contravention.`
  line
  line `(3) If the Controller is satisfied that the essential supply or service was cut off or withheld by the landlord with a view to compel the tenant to vacate the premises or to pay an enhanced rent, the Controller may pass an order directing the landlord to restore the amenities immediately, pending the inquiry referred to in sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `Explanation.--An interim order may be passed under this sub-section without giving notice to the landlord.`
  line
  line `(4) If the Controller on inquiry finds that the essential supply or service enjoyed by the tenant in respect of the premises was cut off or withheld by the landlord without just and sufficient cause, he shall make an order directing the landlord to restore such supply or service.`
  line
  line `(5) The Controller may in his discretion direct that compensation not exceeding fifty rupees--`
  line
  line `(a) be paid to the landlord by the tenant, if the application under sub-section (2) was made frivolously or vexatiously;`
  line
  line `(b) be paid to the tenant by the landlord, if the landlord had cut off or withheld the supply or service without just and sufficient cause.`
  line
  line `Explanation I.--In this section, "essential supply or service" includes supply of water, electricity, lights in passages and on staircases, conservancy and sanitary services.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--For the purposes of this section, withholding any essential supply or service shall include acts or omissions attributable to the landlord on account of which the essential supply or service is cut off by the local authority or any order competent authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (70423)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 56
  title `Landlord’s duty to give notice of new construction to Government.`
  content `Whenever, after the commencement of this Act, any premises are constructed, the landlord shall, within thirty days of the completion of such construction, give intimation thereof in writing to the ^1[Director of Estates] or to such other officer as may be specified in this behalf by the Government.`
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 58 of 1960, s. 3 and Schedule II, for "Estate Officer to the Government of India" (w.e.f. 26-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70423&sectionno=46&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (70424)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 57
  title `Leases of vacant premises to Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 58 of 1960, s. 3 and Schedule II, for "Estate Officer to the Government of India" (w.e.f. 26-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70424&sectionno=47&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this section shall apply only in relation to premises in the areas which, immediately before the 7th day of April, 1958, were included in the New Delhi Municipal Committee and which are, or are intended to be, let for use as a residence.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever any premises the standard rent of which is not less than two thousand and four hundred rupees per year becomes vacant either by the landlord ceasing to occupy the premises or by the termination of a tenancy or by the eviction of a tenant or by the release of the premises from requisition or otherwise, --`
  line
  line `(a) the landlord shall, within seven days of the premises becoming vacant, give intimation thereof in writing to the ^1[Director of Estates];`
  line
  line `(b) whether or not such intimation is given, the ^1[Director of Estates] may serve on the landlord by post or otherwise a notice--`
  line
  line `(i) informing him that the premises are required by the Government for such period as may be specified in the notice; and`
  line
  line `(ii) requiring him, and every person claiming under him, to deliver possession of the premises forthwith to such officer or person as may be specified in the notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the landlord has given the intimation required by clause (a), no notice shall be issued by the 1Director of Estates under clause (b) more than seven days after the delivery to him of the intimation:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing in this sub-section shall apply in respect of any premises the possession of which has been obtained by the landlord on the basis of any order made on the ground set forth in clause (e) of the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 14 or in respect of any premises which have been released from requisition for the use and occupation of the landlord himself.`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (70425)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 58
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 57 of 1988, s. 19, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70425&sectionno=48&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person contravenes any of the provisions of section 5, he shall be punishable--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a contravention of the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 5, with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to a sum which exceeds the unlawful charge claimed or received under that sub-section by one thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a contravention of the provisions of sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of section 5, with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to a sum which exceeds the amount or value of unlawful charge claimed or received under the said sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), as the case may be, by five thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) If any tenant sub-lets, assigns or otherwise parts with the possession of the whole or part of any premises in contravention of the provisions of clause (b) of the proviso to sub-section (1) of section 14, he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) If any landlord re-lets or transfers the whole or any part of any premises in contravention of the provisions of sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 19 he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both.]`
  line
  line `(4) If any landlord contravenes the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 45, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine, or with both.`
  line
  line `(5) If any landlord fails to comply with the provisions of section 46 he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(6) If any person contravenes the provisions of clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 47, or fails to comply with a requirement under clause (b) thereof, he shall be punishable with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (70426)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 59
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70426&sectionno=49&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court inferior to that of a ^1[Metropolitan Magistrate shall try any`
  line `offence punishable under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No court shall take cognizance of an offence punishable under this Act, unless the complaint in`
  line `respect of the offence has been made within three months from the dale of the commission of the offence.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in ^2[section 29 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974)] it shall be lawful for any ^3[Metropolitan Magistrate] to pass a sentence of fine exceeding ^4[five`
  line `thousand rupees] on a person convicted of an offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for [magistrate of the first class] (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 57 of 1988, s. 19, for "Section 32 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)" (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for "magistrate of the first class" (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (70427)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 60
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts barred in respect of certain matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70427&sectionno=50&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save a otherwise expressly`
  line `provided in this Act, no civil court shall entertain any suit or proceeding in so far as it relates to the fixation`
  line `of standard rent in relation to any premises to which this Act applies or to eviction of any tenant therefrom`
  line `or to any other matter which the Controller is empowered by or under this Act to decide, and no injunction`
  line `in respect of any action taken or to be taken by the Controller under this Act shall be granted by any civil`
  line `court or other authority.`
  line
  line `(2) If, immediately before the commencement of this Act, there is any suit or proceeding pending in`
  line `any civil court for the eviction of any tenant from any premises to which this Act applies and the`
  line `construction of which has been completed after the 1st day of June, 1951, but before the 9th day of June,`
  line `1955, such suit or proceeding shall, on such commencement, abate.`
  line
  line `(3) If, in pursuance of any decree or order made by a court, any tenant has been evicted after the 16th`
  line `day of August, 1958, from any premises to which this Act applies and the construction of which has been`
  line `completed after the 1st day of June, 1951, but before the 9th day of June, 1955, then, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any other law, the Controller may, on an application made to him in this behalf by`
  line `such evicted tenant within six months from the date of eviction, direct the landlord to put the tenant in`
  line `possession of the premises or to pay him such compensation as the Controller thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be construed as preventing a civil court from entertaining any suit`
  line `or proceeding for the decision of any question of title to any premises to which this Act applies or any`
  line `question as to the person or persons who are entitled to receive the rent of such premises.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (70428)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 61
  title `Controllers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70428&sectionno=51&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `All Controllers and additional Controllers appointed under`
  line `this Act shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (70429)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 62
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70429&sectionno=52&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against any Controller or additional Controller in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended`
  line `to be done in pursuance of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (70430)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 63
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70430&sectionno=53&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `[Amendment of the Delhi Tenants Temporary Protection Act, 1956.]--Repealed. by The`
  line `Repealing and Amending Act, 1960 (58 of 1960), s. 2 and Schedule. I.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (70431)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 64
  title `Saving of operation of certain enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70431&sectionno=54&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall affect the provisions of the`
  line `Administration of Evacuee Property Act, 1950 (31 of 1950), or the Slum Areas (Improvement and`
  line `Clearance) Act, 1956 (96 of 1956), or the Delhi Tenants (Temporary Protection) Act, 1956 (97 of 1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (70435)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 65
  title `Special provision regarding decrees affected by the Delhi Tenants (Temporary Protection) Act, 1956.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70435&sectionno=55&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Where any decree or order for the recovery of possession of any premises to which the Delhi`
  line `Tenants (Temporary Protection) Act, 1956 (97 of 1956), applies is sought to be executed on the cesser of`
  line `operation of that Act in relation to those premises, the court executing the decree or order may, on the`
  line `application of the person against whom the decree or order has been passed or otherwise, reopen the case`
  line `and if it is satisfied that the decree or order could not have been passed if this Act had been in force on the`
  line `date of the decree or order, the court may, having regard to the provisions of this Act, set aside the decree`
  line `or order or pass such other order in relation thereto as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (70433)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 66
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70433&sectionno=56&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for all or any of the following matters, namely: --`
  line
  line `^1[(a) the manner of approval of valuers and the procedure to be followed by such valuers under the`
  line `proviso to sub-section (2) of section 9;]`
  line
  line `^2[(aa)] the form and manner in which, and the period within which, an application may be made to`
  line `the Controller;`
  line
  line `(b) the form and manner in which an application for deposit or rent may be made and the particulars`
  line `which it may contain;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which a Controller may hold an inquiry under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the powers of the civil court which may be vested in a Controller;`
  line
  line `(e) the form and manner in which an application for appeal or transfer of proceeding may be made`
  line `to the Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of service of notices under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following`
  line `the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule`
  line `or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment`
  line `shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 57 of 1988, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (a) relettered as clause (aa) thereof by s. 20, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 37 of 1984, s. 4, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 26-5-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (70434)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 67
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553&sectionId=70434&sectionno=57&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_5_00115_195859_1666697046553
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Delhi and Ajmer Rent Control Act, 1952 (38 of 1952) in so far as it`
  line `is applicable to the Union territory of Delhi, is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, all suits and other proceedings under the said Act pending, at the`
  line `commencement of this Act, before any court or other authority shall be continued and disposed of in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of the said Act, as if the said Act had continued in force and this Act had`
  line `not been passed:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any such suit or proceeding for the fixation of standard rent or for the eviction of a`
  line `tenant from any premises to which section 54 does not apply, the court or other authority shall have regard`
  line `to the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the provisions for appeal under the said Act shall continue in force in respect of`
  line `suits and proceedings disposed of thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
